My most used product in the house right now is my thermometer.  The Black and Decker team sent over their 3-in-1 InfraredThermometer and it is so loved!  The cold weather ushers in sickness and every virus known to mankind, which means I’m constantly checking everyone's temperature. I love the versatile things such as Forehead mode, In-Ear mode for Kids, Adults, and infants. It can also measure in Object mode for things like milk, food, bath water temperature, and room temperature.  The only way I’m getting through this winter sickness season is with my thermometer and lots of kid snuggles!

Lifestyle Over 40 | The Perfect Bow
The wrapping is just as important as the present.  Here’s how to tie the perfect bow this holiday season
🎅🏼Drape the ribbon on the front of the box down the middle.  Keep one end of the ribbon slightly shorter than the other. 
🎅🏼While keeping your thumb on the ribbon, wrap the long side completely around the box bringing it to the front side of the box. 
🎅🏼Cross the two pieces in the front of the box and rotate the long end on a 45 degree angle
🎅🏼Wrap the long end under and around the box bringing it to the top
🎅🏼While holding the short end tight bring the long end across the center of the box
🎅🏼Tuck the long end under the the crossed ribbon and create a bunny ear
🎅🏼With the remaining slack from the long end creating another bunny ear.  The shorter ribbon will be left hanging to the side.
🎅🏼Tie the bunny ears in a knot
🎅🏼Fluff up the bow and straighten it so it looks perfect!
🎅🏼Snip the ends of the ribbon to shorten them.
